-ant-...\\nE2E_AGENT=factoryai-droid go test -tags=e2e -count=1 -timeout=30m -v \\\\\\n  -run TestE2E_BasicWorkflow ./cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/...\\n```\\n\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"248a5fb6-5023-42d0-b52f-f932c6b9e4e4\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/factoryai-agent\",\"sessionId\":\"4251621e-8574-4598-90f2-c04f09a11525\",\"version\":\"2.1.49\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/factoryai-agent\",\"slug\":\"moonlit-leaping-castle\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_019ShqLfbhfZRx18XxPzSTrZ\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"\\n\\n`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`\\n**BYOK (Bring Your Own Key)** is a pattern where instead of authenticating through a service's proprietary API key, you provide your own API key for the underlying model provider. Here, we're configuring Droid to call Anthropic's API directly via a `customModels` entry in `.factory/settings.json`, which references `${ANTHROPIC_API_KEY}` using Droid's env-var interpolation syntax — so the actual key never touches disk or git.\\n`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`\\n\\nLet me start by reading the files I need to modify.\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":9623,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":23101,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":9623},\"output_tokens\":2,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYThZPUamqqJwtcortj4p\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"f5963c17-9024-41e8-bf34-d1f7b84b9238\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-24T22:41:36.799Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"f5963c17-9024-41e8-bf34-d1f7b84b9238\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/factoryai-agent\",\"sessionId\":\"4251621e-8574-4598-90f2-c04f09a11525\",\"version\":\"2.1.49\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/factoryai