ZdBk2W\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Manual E2E Testing: Factory AI Droid (Interactive Mode)\\n     2→\\n     3→This guide translates every automated E2E test from `cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/` into step-by-step instructions for manual testing with Factory AI Droid in **interactive** mode. The automated tests run agents in non-interactive/exec mode; this guide validates behavior when a human operates Droid interactively with real hooks firing.\\n     4→\\n     5→## Table of Contents\\n     6→\\n     7→- [Prerequisites](#prerequisites)\\n     8→- [Common Setup](#common-setup)\\n     9→- [Basic Workflow Tests](#basic-workflow-tests)\\n    10→  - [Test 1: BasicWorkflow](#test-1-basicworkflow)\\n    11→  - [Test 2: MultipleChanges](#test-2-multiplechanges)\\n    12→- [Checkpoint Tests](#checkpoint-tests)\\n    13→  - [Test 3: CheckpointMetadata](#test-3-checkpointmetadata)\\n    14→  - [Test 4: CheckpointIDFormat](#test-4-checkpointidformat)\\n    15→  - [Test 5: AutoCommitStrategy](#test-5-autocommitstrategy)\\n    16→- [Agent Commits Tests](#agent-commits-tests)\\n    17→  - [Test 6: AgentCommitsDuringTurn](#test-6-agentcommitsduringturn)\\n    18→  - [Test 7: MultipleAgentSessions](#test-7-multipleagentsessions)\\n    19→- [Rewind Tests](#rewind-tests)\\n    20→  - [Test 8: RewindToCheckpoint](#test-8-rewindtocheckpoint)\\n    21→  - [Test 9: RewindAfterCommit](#test-9-rewindaftercommit)\\n    22→  - [Test 10: RewindMultipleFiles](#test-10-rewindmultiplefiles)\\n    23→- [Subagent Tests](#subagent-tests)\\n    24→  - [Test 11: SubagentCheckpoint](#test-11-subagentcheckpoint)\\n    25→  - [Test 12: SubagentCheckpoint_CommitFlow](#test-12-subagentcheckpoint_commitflow)\\n    26→- [Checkpoint Workflow Scenarios](#checkpoint-workflow-scenarios)\\n    27→  - [Test 13: Scenario 1 – Basic Flow](#test-13-scenario-1--basic-flow)\\n    28→  - [Test 14: Scenario 2 – Agent Commits During Turn](#test-14-scenario-2--agent-commits-during-turn)\\n    29→  - [Test 15: Scenario 3 – Multiple Granular Commits](#test-15-scenario-3--multiple-granular-commits)\\n    30→  - [Test 16: Scenario 4 – User Splits Commits](#test-16-scenario-4--user-splits-commits)\\n    31→  - [Test 17: Scenario 5 – Partial Commit + Stash + Next Prompt](#test-17-scenario-5--partial-commit--stash--next-prompt)\\n    32→  - [Test 18: Scenario 6 – Stash + Second Prompt + Unstash + Commit All](#test-18-scenario-6--stash--second-prompt--unstash--commit-all)\\n    33→  - [Test 19: Scenario 7 – Partial Staging (Simulated)](#test-19-scenario-7--partial-staging-simulated)\\n    34→- [Content-Aware Detection Tests](#content-aware-detection-tests)\\n    35→  - [Test 20: ContentAwareOverlap_RevertAndReplace](#test-20-contentawareoverlap_revertandreplace)\\n    36→- [Existing Files Tests](#existing-files-tests)\\n    37→  - [Test 21: ExistingFiles_ModifyAndCommit](#test-21-existingfiles_modifyandcommit)\\n    38→  - [Test 22: ExistingFiles_StashModifications](#test-22-existingfiles_stashmodifications)\\n    39→  - [Test 23: ExistingFiles_SplitCommits](#test-23-existingfiles_splitcommits)\\n    40→  - [Test 24: ExistingFiles_RevertModification](#test-24-existingfiles_revertmodification)\\n    41→  - [Test 25: ExistingFiles_MixedNewAndModified](#test-25-existingfiles_mixednewandmodified)\\n    42→- [Session Lifecycle Tests](#session-lifecycle-tests)\\n    43→  - [Test 26: EndedSession_UserCommitsAfterExit](#test-26-endedsession_usercommitsafterexit)\\n    44→  - [Test 27: DeletedFiles_CommitDeletion](#test-27-deletedfiles_commitdeletion)\\n    45→  - [Test 28: AgentCommitsMidTurn_UserCommitsRemainder](#test-28-agentcommitsmidturn_usercommitsremainder)\\n    46→  - [Test 29: TrailerRemoval_SkipsCondensation](#test-29-trailerremoval_skipscondensation)\\n    47→  - [Test 30: SessionDepleted_ManualEditNoCheckpoint](#test-30-sessiondepleted_manualeditnocheckpoint)\\n    48→- [Resume Tests](#resume-tests)\\n    49→  - [Test 31: ResumeInRelocatedRepo](#test-31-resumeinrelocatedrepo)\\n    50→\\n    51→---\\n    52→\\n    53→## Prerequisites\\n    54→\\n    55→1. **Entire CLI** built and in your `$PATH`:\\n    56→   ```bash\\n    57→   cd /path/to/cli-repo\\n    58→   go build -o ~/go/bin/entire ./cmd/entire\\n    59→   ```\\n    60→\\n    61→2. **Factory AI Droid** installed and authenticated:\\n    62→   ```bash\\n    63→   droid --version          # Verify installed\\n    64→   echo $FACTORY_API_KEY    # Must be set\\n    65→   ```\\n    66→\\n    67→3. **Git** configured with a user name and email (for commits):\\n    68→   ```bash\\n    69→   git config --global user.name \\\"Test User\\\"\\n    70→   git config --global user.email \\\"test@example.com\\\"\\n    71→   ```\\n    72→\\n    73→4. **jq** installed (for inspecting JSON output):\\n    74→   ```bash\\n    75→   jq --version\\n    76→   ```\\n    77→\\n    78→---\\n    79→\\n    80→## Common Setup\\n    81→\\n    82→Every test starts from a clean test repository. Run these steps before each test (or use the helper script at the bottom).\\n    83→\\n    84→```bash\\n    85→# Create a fresh test repo\\n    86→TEST_DIR=$(mktemp -d)\\n    87→cd \\\"$TEST_DIR\\\"\\n    88→git init\\n    89→git commit --allow-empty -m \\\"Initial commit\\\"\\n    90→git checkout -b feature/manual-test\\n    91→\\n    92→# Enable entire with droid agent (default: manual-commit strategy)\\n    93→entire enable --agent factoryai-droid --strategy manual-commit --telemetry=false --force\\n    94→\\n    95→# Commit the config files so they survive stash operations\\n    96→git add .\\n    97→git commit -m \\\"Add entire and agent config\\\"\\n    98→```\\n    99→\\n   100→For **auto-commit strategy** tests, replace `--strategy manual-commit` with `--strategy auto-commit`.\\n   101→\\n   102→### Starting Droid Interactively\\n   103→\\n   104→```bash\\n   105→# Launch droid in interactive mode (in the test repo)\\n   106→droid\\n   107→```\\n   108→\\n   109→When Droid starts, entire's hooks fire via the `.factory/settings.json` configuration. You type prompts directly in Droid's interactive session.\\n   110→\\n   111→### Verification Commands Reference\\n   112→\\n   113→These commands are used throughout the tests for verification:\\n   114→\\n   115→| Command | Purpose |\\n   116→|---------|---------|\\n   117→| `entire rewind --list` | List available rewind points (JSON) |\\n   118→| `entire rewind --list \\\\| jq .` | Pretty-print rewind points |\\n   119→| `entire rewind --to <ID>` | Rewind to a specific checkpoint |\\n   120→| `git log --oneline` | Check commit history |\\n   121→| `git log -1 --format=%B` | Show full message of latest commit |\\n   122→| `git log --format=%B \\\\| grep \\\"Entire-Checkpoint:\\\"` | Find checkpoint trailers |\\n   123→| `git branch -a \\\\| grep entire` | List entire-related branches |\\n   124→| `git show entire/checkpoints/v1:<path>` | Read metadata from checkpoint branch |\\n   125→| `git status` | Check working tree status |\\n   126→\\n   127→---\\n   128→\\n   129→## Basic Workflow Tests\\n   130→\\n   131→### Test 1: BasicWorkflow\\n   132→\\n   133→**What it validates:** The fundamental workflow — agent creates a file, user commits, checkpoint is created.\\n   134→\\n   135→**Corresponds to:** `TestE2E_BasicWorkflow`\\n   136→\\n   137→#### Steps\\n   138→\\n   139→1. [Common Setup](#common-setup) with `manual-commit` strategy.\\n   140→\\n   141→2. **Start Droid** and type this prompt:\\n   142→   ```\\n   143→   Create a file called hello.go with a simple Go program that prints \\\"Hello, World!\\\".\\n   144→   Use package main, a main function, and fmt.Println. No comments, tests, or extra files.\\n   145→   ```\\n   146→\\n   147→3. **Wait for Droid to finish**, then exit Droid (Ctrl+C or `/exit`).\\n   148→\\n   149→4. **Verify the file was created:**\\n   150→   ```bash\\n   151→   cat hello.go\\n   152→   # Should contain: package main, func main(), fmt.Println(\\\"Hello, World!\\\")\\n   153→   ```\\n   154→\\n   155→5. **Check rewind points exist:**\\n   156→   ```bash\\n   157→   entire rewind --list | jq .\\n   158→   # Should have at least 1 rewind point\\n   159→   ```\\n   160→\\n   161→6. **Commit the file with hooks:**\\n   162→   ```bash\\n   163→   git add hello.go\\n   164→   git commit -m \\\"Add hello world program\\\"\\n   165→   ```\\n   166→   The prepare-commit-msg hook should add an `Entire-Checkpoint` trailer.\\n   167→\\n   168→7. **Verify checkpoint trailer:**\\n   169→   ```bash\\n   170→   git log -1 --format=%B | grep \\\"Entire-Checkpoint:\\\"\\n   171→   # Should print: Entire-Checkpoint: <12-hex-char ID>\\n   172→   ```\\n   173→\\n   174→8. **Verify metadata branch exists:**\\n   175→   ```bash\\n   176→   git branch -a | grep \\\"entire/checkpoints/v1\\\"\\n   177→   # Should show the branch\\n   178→   ```\\n   179→\\n   180→#### Expected Outcome\\n   181→- `hello.go` exists with a valid Hello World program\\n   182→- At least 1 rewind point before commit\\n   183→- Commit has `Entire-Checkpoint` trailer with 12-hex-char ID\\n   184→- `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch exists\\n   185→\\n   186→---\\n   187→\\n   188→### Test 2: MultipleChanges\\n   189→\\n   190→**What it validates:** Multiple agent changes across separate prompts before a single commit.\\n   191→\\n   192→**Corresponds to:** `TestE2E_MultipleChanges`\\n   193→\\n   194→#### Steps\\n   195→\\n   196→1. [Common Setup](#common-setup) with `manual-commit` strategy.\\n   197→\\n   198→2. **Start Droid** and type:\\n   199→   ```\\n   200→   Create a file called hello.go with a simple Go program that prints \\\"Hello, World!\\\".\\n   201→   Use package main, a main function, and fmt.Println. No comments, tests, or extra files.\\n   202→   ```\\n   203→\\n   204→3. **After Droid finishes the first prompt**, type a second prompt:\\n   205→   ```\\n   206→   Create a file called calc.go with two exported functions:\\n   207→   Add(a, b int) int - returns a + b\\n   208→   Subtract(a, b int) int - returns a - b\\n   209→   Use package main. No comments, no main function, no tests, no other files.\\n   210→   ```\\n   211→\\n   212→4. **Exit Droid**, then verify both files:\\n   213→   ```bash\\n   214→   ls hello.go calc.go\\n   215→   ```\\n   216→\\n   217→5. **Check rewind points:**\\n   218→   ```bash\\n   219→   entire rewind --list | jq 'length'\\n   220→   # Should be at least 2\\n   221→   ```\\n   222→\\n   223→6. **Commit both files:**\\n   224→   ```bash\\n   225→   git add hello.go calc.go\\n   226→   git commit -m \\\"Add hello world and calculator\\\"\\n   227→   ```\\n   228→\\n   229→7. **Verify checkpoint:**\\n   230→   ```bash\\n   231→   git log -1 --format=%B | grep \\\"Entire-Checkpoint:\\\"\\n   232→   ```\\n   233→\\n   234→#### Expected Outcome\\n   235→- Both `hello.go` and `calc.go` exist\\n   236→- At least 2 rewind points\\n   237→- Commit has checkpoint trailer\\n   238→\\n   239→---\\n   240→\\n   241→## Checkpoint Tests\\n   242→\\n   243→### Test 3: CheckpointMetadata\\n   244→\\n   245→**What it validates:** Checkpoint metadata is correctly stored and accessible.\\n   246→\\n   247→**Corresponds to:** `TestE2E_CheckpointMetadata`\\n   248→\\n   249→#### Steps\\n   250→\\n   251→1. [Common Setup](#common-setup) with `manual-commit` strategy.\\n   252→\\n   253→2. **Start Droid** and type:\\n   254→   ```\\n   255→   Create a file called config.json with this exact content:\\n   256→   {\\\"name\\\": \\\"e2e-test\\\", \\\"version\\\": \\\"1.0.0\\\", \\\"enabled\\\": true}\\n   257→   Do not create any other files.\\n   258→   ```\\n   259→\\n   260→3. **Exit Droid**, then check rewind points:\\n   261→   ```bash\\n   262→   entire rewind --list | jq '.[0] | {id, metadata_dir, message}'\\n   263→   # Each point should have an id and metadata_dir\\n   264→   ```\\n   265→\\n   266→4. **Commit:**\\n   267→   ```bash\\n   268→   git add config.json\\n   269→   git commit -m \\\"Add config file\\\"\\n   270→   ```\\n   271→\\n   272→5. **Extract checkpoint ID:**\\n   273→   ```bash\\n   274→   CPID=$(git log -1 --format=%B | grep \\\"Entire-Checkpoint:\\\" | awk '{print $2}')\\n   275→   echo \\\"Checkpoint ID: $CPID\\\"\\n   276→   ```\\n   277→\\n   278→6. **Verify metadata on checkpoint branch:**\\n   279→   ```bash\\n   280→   # Compute sharded path: first 2 chars / remaining chars\\n   281→   SHARD=\\\"${CPID:0:2}/${CPID:2}\\\"\\n   282→   git show \\\"entire/checkpoints/v1:${SHARD}/metadata.json\\\" | jq .\\n   283→   # Should contain: checkpoint_id, strategy, sessions, files_touched\\n   284→   ```\\n   285→\\n   286→7. **Verify session metadata:**\\n   287→   ```bash\\n   288→   git show \\\"entire/checkpoints/v1:${SHARD}/0/metadata.json\\\" | jq .\\n   289→   # Should contain: checkpoint_id, created_at\\n   290→   ```\\n   291→\\n   292→8. **Check post-commit rewind points:**\\n   293→   ```bash\\n   294→   entire rewind --list | jq '.[] | {id, is_logs_only, condensation_id}'\\n   295→   # Should show logs-only points after commit\\n   296→   ```\\n   297→\\n   298→#### Expected Outcome\\n   299→- Rewind points have `metadata_dir` set\\n   300→- Checkpoint metadata on `entire/checkpoints/v1` contains `checkpoint_id`, `strategy`, `files_touched`\\n   301→- Session subfolder `0/` contains `metadata.json` with `created_at`\\n   302→- Post-commit points are marked `is_logs_only: true`\\n   303→\\n   304→---\\n   305→\\n   306→### Test 4: CheckpointIDFormat\\n   307→\\n   308→**What it validates:** Checkpoint IDs are exactly 12 lowercase hex characters.\\n   309→\\n   310→**Corresponds to:** `TestE2E_CheckpointIDFormat`\\n   311→\\n   312→#### Steps\\n   313→\\n   314→1. [Common Setup](#common-setup) with `manual-commit` strategy.\\n   315→\\n   316→2. **Start Droid**, create `hello.go` (any simple Go program), exit Droid.\\n   317→\\n   318→3. **Commit:**\\n   319→   ```bash\\n   320→   git add hello.go\\n   321→   git commit -m \\\"Add hello world\\\"\\n   322→   ```\\n   323→\\n   324→4. **Validate checkpoint ID format:**\\n   325→   ```bash\\n   326→   CPID=$(git log -1 --format=%B | grep \\\"Entire-Checkpoint:\\\" | awk '{print $2}')\\n   327→   echo \\\"Checkpoint ID: '$CPID'\\\"\\n   328→   echo \\\"Length: ${#CPID}\\\"\\n   329→   echo \\\"$CPID\\\" | grep -qE '^[0-9a-f]{12}$' && echo \\\"PASS: Valid format\\\" || echo \\\"FAIL: Invalid format\\\"\\n   330→   ```\\n   331→\\n   332→#### Expected Outcome\\n   333→- Checkpoint ID is exactly 12 characters\\n   334→- Only contains lowercase hex characters (`0-9`, `a-f`)\\n   335→\\n   336→---\\n   337→\\n   338→### Test 5: AutoCommitStrategy\\n   339→\\n   340→**What it validates:** Auto-commit strategy creates commits automatically when Droid finishes.\\n   341→\\n   342→**Corresponds to:** `TestE2E_AutoCommitStrategy`\\n   343→\\n   344→#### Steps\\n   345→\\n   346→1. [Common Setup](#common-setup) but with **auto-commit** strategy:\\n   347→   ```bash\\n   348→   entire enable --agent factoryai-droid --strategy auto-commit --telemetry=false --force\\n   349→   ```\\n   350→\\n   351→2. **Count commits before:**\\n   352→   ```bash\\n   353→   git log --oneline | wc -l\\n   354→   ```\\n   355→\\n   356→3. **Start Droid** and type:\\n   357→   ```\\n   358→   Create a file called hello.go with a simple Go program that prints \\\"Hello, World!\\\".\\n   359→   Use package main, a main function, and fmt.Println. No comments, tests, or extra files.\\n   360→   ```\\n   361→\\n   362→4. **Exit Droid**, then count commits after:\\n   363→   ```bash\\n   364→   git log --oneline | wc -l\\n   365→   # Should be more than before\\n   366→   ```\\n   367→\\n   368→5. **Verify checkpoint in commit:**\\n   369→   ```bash\\n   370→   CPID=$(git log --format=%B | grep \\\"Entire-Checkpoint:\\\" | head -1 | awk '{print $2}')\\n   371→   echo \\\"Checkpoint ID: $CPID\\\"\\n   372→   echo ${#CPID}  # Should be 12\\n   373→   ```\\n   374→\\n   375→6. **Verify metadata branch and rewind points:**\\n   376→   ```bash\\n   377→   git branch -a | grep \\\"entire/checkpoints/v1\\\"\\n   378→   entire rewind --list | jq 'length'\\n   379→   ```\\n   380→\\n   381→#### Expected Outcome\\n   382→- Commit count increased (auto-commit created commits)\\n   383→- Checkpoint trailer present with 12-hex-char ID\\n   384→- `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch exists\\n   385→- At least 1 rewind point\\n   386→\\n   387→---\\n   388→\\n   389→## Agent Commits Tests\\n   390→\\n   391→### Test 6: AgentCommitsDuringTurn\\n   392→\\n   393→**What it validates:** Behavior when the agent commits during its turn (deferred finalization).\\n   394→\\n   395→**Corresponds to:** `TestE2E_AgentCommitsDuringTurn`\\n   396→\\n   397→#### Steps\\n   398→\\n   399→1. [Common Setup](#common-setup) with `manual-commit` strategy.\\n   400→\\n   401→2. **Start Droid** and type:\\n   402→   ```\\n   403→   Create a file called hello.go with a simple Go program that prints \\\"Hello, World!\\\".\\n   404→   Use package main, a main function, and fmt.Println. No comments, tests, or extra files.\\n   405→   ```\\n   406→\\n   407→3. **After Droid finishes**, type a second prompt telling Droid to commit:\\n   408→   ```\\n   409→   Stage and commit the hello.go file with commit message \\\"Add hello world via agent\\\".\\n   410→   Use these exact commands:\\n   411→   1. git add hello.go\\n   412→   2. git commit -m \\\"Add hello world via agent\\\"\\n   413→   Only run these two commands, nothing else.\\n   414→   ```\\n   415→\\n   416→4. **After Droid finishes the commit**, verify it was made:\\n   417→   ```bash\\n   418→   git log -1 --format=\\\"%s\\\"\\n   419→   # Should show the commit message\\n   420→   ```\\n   421→\\n   422→5. **Check rewind points:**\\n   423→   ```bash\\n   424→   entire rewind --list | jq 'length'\\n   425→   ```\\n   426→\\n   427→6. **Still in the same Droid session**, type another prompt:\\n   428→   ```\\n   429→   Create a file called calc.go with two exported functions:\\n   430→   Add(a, b int) int - returns a + b\\n   431→   Subtract(a, b int) int - returns a - b\\n   432→   Use package main. No comments, no main function, no tests, no other files.\\n   433→   ```\\n   434→\\n   435→7. **Exit Droid**, then commit the second file:\\n   436→   ```bash\\n   437→   git add calc.go\\n   438→   git commit -m \\\"Add calculator\\\"\\n   439→   ```\\n   440→\\n   441→8. **Check checkpoint in latest commit:**\\n   442→   ```bash\\n   443→   git log -1 --format=%B | grep \\\"Entire-Checkpoint:\\\"\\n   444→   ```\\n   445→\\n   446→#### Expected Outcome\\n   447→- Agent-initiated commit is made during the turn\\n   448→- Rewind points exist after agent commit\\n   449→- User's subsequent commit gets checkpoint trailer\\n   450→- Both files exist (`hello.go`, `calc.go`)\\n   451→\\n   452→---\\n   453→\\n   454→### Test 7: MultipleAgentSessions\\n   455→\\n   456→**What it validates:** Behavior across multiple separate agent sessions with commits between them.\\n   457→\\n   458→**Corresponds to:** `TestE2E_MultipleAgentSessions`\\n   459→\\n   460→#### Steps\\n   461→\\n   462→1. [Common Setup](#common-setup) with `manual-commit` strategy.\\n   463→\\n   464→2. **Session 1:** Start Droid, create `hello.go`, exit Droid.\\n   465→   ```bash\\n   466→   # In Droid:\\n   467→   # Create a file called hello.go with a simple Go program that prints \\\"Hello, World!\\\".\\n   468→   ```\\n   469→   ```bash\\n   470→   git add hello.go && git commit -m \\\"Session 1: Add hello world\\\"\\n   471→   ```\\n   472→\\n   473→3. **Session 2:** Start Droid again, create `calc.go`, exit Droid.\\n   474→   ```bash\\n   475→   # In Droid:\\n   476→   # Create calc.go with Add(a, b int) int and Subtract(a, b int) int functions.\\n   477→   ```\\n   478→   ```bash\\n   479→   git add calc.go && git commit -m \\\"Session 2: Add calculator\\\"\\n   480→   ```\\n   481→\\n   482→4. **Session 3:** Start Droid again, add Multiply to `calc.go`, exit Droid.\\n   483→   ```bash\\n   484→   # In Droid:\\n   485→   # Add a Multiply function to calc.go: Multiply(a, b int) int\\n   486→   ```\\n   487→   ```bash\\n   488→   git add calc.go && git commit -m \\\"Session 3: Add multiply function\\\"\\n   489→   ```\\n   490→\\n   491→5. **Verify all checkpoint IDs are present and unique:**\\n   492→   ```bash\\n   493→   git log --format=%B | grep \\\"Entire-Checkpoint:\\\" | awk '{print $2}'\\n   494→   # Should show 3 different checkpoint IDs\\n   495→   ```\\n   496→\\n   497→#### Expected Outcome\\n   498→- Three separate commits, each with unique checkpoint IDs\\n   499→- `calc.go` contains `Add`, `Subtract`, and `Multiply` functions\\n   500→- Each session creates and condenses its own checkpoints\\n   501→\\n   502→---\\n   503→\\n   504→## Rewind Tests\\n   505→\\n   506→### Test 8: RewindToCheckpoint\\n   507→\\n   508→**What it validates:** Rewinding to a previous checkpoint restores file content.\\n   509→\\n   510→**Corresponds to:** `TestE2E_RewindToCheckpoint`\\n   511→\\n   512→#### Steps\\n   513→\\n   514→1. [Common Setup](#common-setup) with `manual-commit` strategy.\\n   515→\\n   516→2. **Start Droid** and create `hello.go`:\\n   517→   ```\\n   518→   Create a file called hello.go with a simple Go program that prints \\\"Hello, World!\\\".\\n   519→   ```\\n   520→\\n   521→3. **Save the first checkpoint ID:**\\n   522→   ```bash\\n   523→   # While still in Droid or after it runs, check rewind points in another terminal:\\n   524→   FIRST_ID=$(entire rewind --list | jq -r '.[0].id')\\n   525→   echo \\\"First checkpoint: $FIRST_ID\\\"\\n   526→   ```\\n   527→\\n   528→4. **Save the original content:**\\n   529→   ```bash\\n   530→   cat hello.go  # Note the content\\n   531→   ```\\n   532→\\n   533→5. **In Droid, modify the file:**\\n   534→   ```\\n   535→   Modify hello.go to print \\\"Hello, E2E Test!\\\" instead of \\\"Hello, World!\\\".\\n   536→   Do not add any other functionality or files.\\n   537→   ```\\n   538→\\n   539→6. **Verify content changed:**\\n   540→   ```bash\\n   541→   cat hello.go  # Should now contain \\\"E2E Test\\\"\\n   542→   ```\\n   543→\\n   544→7. **Exit Droid**, then verify we have at least 2 rewind points:\\n   545→   ```bash\\n   546→   entire rewind --list | jq 'length'\\n   547→   ```\\n   548→\\n   549→8. **Rewind to the first checkpoint:**\\n   550→   ```bash\\n   551→   entire rewind --to \\\"$FIRST_ID\\\"\\n   552→   ```\\n   553→\\n   554→9. **Verify content was restored:**\\n   555→   ```bash\\n   556→   cat hello.go  # Should be back to \\\"Hello, World!\\\"\\n   557→   grep -q \\\"E2E Test\\\" hello.go && echo \\\"FAIL\\\" || echo \\\"PASS: Content restored\\\"\\n   558→   ```\\n   559→\\n   560→#### Expected Outcome\\n   561→- After rewind, `hello.go` contains the original \\\"Hello, World!\\\" content\\n   562→- The \\\"E2E Test\\\" modification is gone\\n   563→\\n   564→---\\n   565→\\n   566→### Test 9: RewindAfterCommit\\n   567→\\n   568→**What it validates:** Pre-commit checkpoint IDs become invalid after commit (shadow branch is deleted).\\n   569→\\n   570→**Corresponds to:** `TestE2E_RewindAfterCommit`\\n   571→\\n   572→#### Steps\\n   573→\\n   574→1. [Common Setup](#common-setup) with `manual-commit` strategy.\\n   575→\\n   576→2. **Start Droid**, create `hello.go`, exit Droid.\\n   577→\\n   578→3. **Record the pre-commit rewind point:**\\n   579→   ```bash\\n   580→   PRE_ID=$(entire rewind --list | jq -r '.[0].id')\\n   581→   IS_LOGS_ONLY=$(entire rewind --list | jq -r '.[0].is_logs_only')\\n   582→   echo \\\"Pre-commit ID: $PRE_ID (is_logs_only: $IS_LOGS_ONLY)\\\"\\n   583→   # is_logs_only should be false (it's on the shadow branch)\\n   584→   ```\\n   585→\\n   586→4. **Commit (triggers condensation and shadow branch deletion):**\\n   587→   ```bash\\n   588→   git add hello.go\\n   589→   git commit -m \\\"Add hello world\\\"\\n   590→   ```\\n   591→\\n   592→5. **Check post-commit rewind points:**\\n   593→   ```bash\\n   594→   entire rewind --list | jq '.[] | {id, is_logs_only, condensation_id}'\\n   595→   # Should show logs-only point(s) with DIFFERENT IDs than pre-commit\\n   596→   ```\\n   597→\\n   598→6. **Attempt rewind to the OLD pre-commit ID:**\\n   599→   ```bash\\n   600→   entire rewind --to \\\"$PRE_ID\\\" 2>&1\\n   601→   # Should FAIL with \\\"not found\\\" error\\n   602→   ```\\n   603→\\n   604→#### Expected Outcome\\n   605→- Pre-commit checkpoint is NOT logs-only\\n   606→- Post-commit checkpoints have different IDs and ARE logs-only\\n   607→- Rewind to old shadow branch ID fails with \\\"not found\\\"\\n   608→\\n   609→---\\n   610→\\n   611→### Test 10: RewindMultipleFiles\\n   612→\\n   613→**What it validates:** Rewinding restores/removes files across multiple file changes.\\n   614→\\n   615→**Corresponds to:** `TestE2E_RewindMultipleFiles`\\n   616→\\n   617→#### Steps\\n   618→\\n   619→1. [Common Setup](#common-setup) with `manual-commit` strategy.\\n   620→\\n   621→2. **Start Droid** and create the first file:\\n   622→   ```\\n   623→   Create a file called hello.go with a simple Go program that prints \\\"Hello, World!\\\".\\n   624→   ```\\n   625→\\n   626→3. **Record the checkpoint after the first file:**\\n   627→   ```bash\\n   628→   AFTER_FIRST=$(entire rewind --list | jq -r '.[0].id')\\n   629→   echo \\\"After first file: $AFTER_FIRST\\\"\\n   630→   ```\\n   631→\\n   632→4. **In Droid, create the second file:**\\n   633→   ```\\n   634→   Create a file called calc.go with Add(a, b int) int and Subtract(a, b int) int functions.\\n   635→   Use package main. No comments, no main, no tests.\\n   636→   ```\\n   637→\\n   638→5. **Exit Droid and verify both files exist:**\\n   639→   ```bash\\n   640→   ls hello.go calc.go\\n   641→   ```\\n   642→\\n   643→6. **Rewind to after first file (before second):**\\n   644→   ```bash\\n   645→   entire rewind --to \\\"$AFTER_FIRST\\\"\\n   646→   ```\\n   647→\\n   648→7. **Verify only the first file exists:**\\n   649→   ```bash\\n   650→   ls hello.go && echo \\\"PASS: hello.go exists\\\"\\n   651→   ls calc.go 2>/dev/null && echo \\\"FAIL: calc.go should not exist\\\" || echo \\\"PASS: calc.go removed\\\"\\n   652→   ```\\n   653→\\n   654→#### Expected Outcome\\n   655→- `hello.go` still exists after rewind\\n   656→- `calc.go` is removed by the rewind\\n   657→\\n   658→---\\n   659→\\n   660→## Subagent Tests\\n   661→\\n   662→> **Note:** These tests are Claude Code-specific (Task tool). For Droid, adapt them to test whether Droid's subagent/tool usage creates task checkpoints. If Droid does not support a Task tool equivalent, these tests verify that regular checkpoints are still created.\\n   663→\\n   664→### Test 11: SubagentCheckpoint\\n   665→\\n   666→**What it validates:** Subagent/task checkpoint creation when Droid delegates work.\\n   667→\\n   668→**Corresponds to:** `TestE2E_SubagentCheckpoint`\\n   669→\\n   670→#### Steps\\n   671→\\n   672→1. [Common Setup](#common-setup) with `manual-commit` strategy.\\n   673→\\n   674→2. **Start Droid** and type a prompt that may trigger subagent usage:\\n   675→   ```\\n   676→   Create a file called subagent_output.txt containing the text \\\"Created by subagent\\\".\\n   677→   ```\\n   678→\\n   679→3. **Exit Droid** and check results:\\n   680→   ```bash\\n   681→   cat subagent_output.txt 2>/dev/null || echo \\\"File not created\\\"\\n   682→   ```\\n   683→\\n   684→4. **Check rewind points:**\\n   685→   ```bash\\n   686→   entire rewind --list | jq '.[] | {id, is_task_checkpoint, tool_use_id, message}'\\n   687→   ```\\n   688→\\n   689→5. **Look for task checkpoints (if any):**\\n   690→   ```bash\\n   691→   entire rewind --list | jq '[.[] | select(.is_task_checkpoint == true)] | length'\\n   692→   ```\\n   693→\\n   694→#### Expected Outcome\\n   695→- At least one checkpoint exists (task or regular)\\n   696→- If Droid used a subagent, `is_task_checkpoint: true` points may appear\\n   697→- If not, regular checkpoints should still exist\\n   698→\\n   699→---\\n   700→\\n   701→### Test 12: SubagentCheckpoint_CommitFlow\\n   702→\\n   703→**What it validates:** Task checkpoints are properly handled through the commit flow.\\n   704→\\n   705→**Corresponds to:** `TestE2E_SubagentCheckpoint_CommitFlow`\\n   706→\\n   707→#### Steps\\n   708→\\n   709→1. Follow [Test 11](#test-11-subagentcheckpoint) steps 1-4.\\n   710→\\n   711→2. **If a file was created, commit it:**\\n   712→   ```bash\\n   713→   git add subagent_output.txt\\n   714→   git commit -m \\\"Add subagent output\\\"\\n   715→   ```\\n   716→\\n   717→3. **Verify checkpoint:**\\n   718→   ```bash\\n   719→   CPID=$(git log -1 --format=%B | grep \\\"Entire-Checkpoint:\\\" | awk '{print $2}')\\n   720→   echo \\\"Checkpoint ID: $CPID\\\"\\n   721→   ```\\n   722→\\n   723→4. **Validate checkpoint on metadata branch:**\\n   724→   ```bash\\n   725→   SHARD=\\\"${CPID:0:2}/${CPID:2}\\\"\\n   726→   git show \\\"entire/checkpoints/v1:${SHARD}/metadata.json\\\" | jq .\\n   727→   ```\\n   728→\\n   729→5. **Verify logs-only point after commit:**\\n   730→   ```bash\\n   731→   entire rewind --list | jq '.[] | select(.is_logs_only == true)'\\n   732→   ```\\n   733→\\n   734→#### Expected Outcome\\n   735→- Commit has checkpoint trailer\\n   736→- Metadata exists on `entire/checkpoints/v1`\\n   737→- Post-commit shows logs-only rewind point\\n   738→\\n   739→---\\n   740→\\n   741→## Checkpoint Workflow Scenarios\\n   742→\\n   743→These tests correspond to the scenarios documented in `docs/architecture/checkpoint-scenarios.md`.\\n   744→\\n   745→### Test 13: Scenario 1 – Basic Flow\\n   746→\\n   747→**What it validates:** The simplest documented workflow: Prompt → Changes → Prompt Finishes → User Commits.\\n   748→\\n   749→**Corresponds to:** `TestE2E_Scenario1_BasicFlow`\\n   750→\\n   751→#### Steps\\n   752→\\n   753→1. [Common Setup](#common-setup) with `manual-commit` strategy.\\n   754→\\n   755→2. **Start Droid** and type:\\n   756→   ```\\n   757→   Create a file called scenario1.go with this content:\\n   758→   package main\\n   759→   func Scenario1() {}\\n   760→   Create only this file.\\n   761→   ```\\n   762→\\n   763→3. **Exit Droid**, then verify:\\n   764→   ```bash\\n   765→   cat scenario1.go\\n   766→   entire rewind --list | jq 'length'  # At least 1\\n   767→   ```\\n   768→\\n   769→4. **Commit:**\\n   770→   ```bash\\n   771→   git add scenario1.go\\n   772→   git commit -m \\\"Add scenario1 file\\\"\\n   773→   ```\\n   774→\\n   775→5. **Verify checkpoint and metadata:**\\n   776→   ```bash\\n   777→   CPID=$(git log -1 --format=%B | grep \\\"Entire-Checkpoint:\\\" | awk '{print $2}')\\n   778→   SHARD=\\\"${CPID:0:2}/${CPID:2}\\\"\\n   779→\\n   780→   # Verify metadata\\n   781→   git show \\\"entire/checkpoints/v1:${SHARD}/metadata.json\\\" | jq '{\\n   782→     checkpoint_id, strategy, files_touched\\n   783→   }'\\n   784→   # files_touched should include \\\"scenario1.go\\\"\\n   785→   # strategy should be \\\"manual-commit\\\"\\n   786→\\n   787→   # Verify transcript exists\\n   788→   git show \\\"entire/checkpoints/v1:${SHARD}/0/full.jsonl\\\" | head -1 | jq . >/dev/null && echo \\\"PASS: Valid JSONL\\\"\\n   789→   ```\\n   790→\\n   791→6. **Verify shadow branch was cleaned up:**\\n   792→   ```bash\\n   793→   git branch -a | grep \\\"entire/\\\" | grep -v \\\"checkpoints\\\"\\n   794→   # Should be empty (no shadow branches remain)\\n   795→   ```\\n   796→\\n   797→#### Expected Outcome\\n   798→- Checkpoint links to metadata with `files_touched: [\\\"scenario1.go\\\"]`\\n   799→- Transcript exists and is valid JSONL\\n   800→- No shadow branches remain after condensation\\n   801→\\n   802→---\\n   803→\\n   804→### Test 14: Scenario 2 – Agent Commits During Turn\\n   805→\\n   806→**What it validates:** Deferred finalization when agent commits during ACTIVE phase.\\n   807→\\n   808→**Corresponds to:** `TestE2E_Scenario2_AgentCommitsDuringTurn`\\n   809→\\n   810→#### Steps\\n   811→\\n   812→1. [Common Setup](#common-setup) with `manual-commit` strategy.\\n   813→\\n   814→2. **Record commit count:**\\n   815→   ```bash\\n   816→   git log --oneline | wc -l\\n   817→   ```\\n   818→\\n   819→3. **Start Droid** and type:\\n   820→   ```\\n   821→   Create a file called agent_commit.go with this content:\\n   822→   package main\\n   823→   func AgentCommit() {}\\n   824→\\n   825→   Then commit it with: git add agent_commit.go && git commit -m \\\"Agent adds file\\\"\\n   826→\\n   827→   Create the file first, then run the git commands.\\n   828→   ```\\n   829→\\n   830→4. **Exit Droid**, then verify:\\n   831→   ```bash\\n   832→   cat agent_commit.go\\n   833→   git log --oneline | wc -l  # Should be more than before\\n   834→   git log -1 --format=\\\"%s\\\"   # Check commit message\\n   835→   ```\\n   836→\\n   837→5. **Check for checkpoint trailer:**\\n   838→   ```bash\\n   839→   git log --format=%B | grep \\\"Entire-Checkpoint:\\\" | head -1\\n   840→   ```\\n   841→\\n   842→6. **If checkpoint exists, validate metadata:**\\n   843→   ```bash\\n   844→   CPID=$(git log --format=%B | grep \\\"Entire-Checkpoint:\\\" | head -1 | awk '{print $2}')\\n   845→   if [ -n \\\"$CPID\\\" ]; then\\n   846→     SHARD=\\\"${CPID:0:2}/${CPID:2}\\\"\\n   847→     git show \\\"entire/checkpoints/v1:${SHARD}/metadata.json\\\" | jq '{files_touched}'\\n   848→     # Should include \\\"agent_commit.go\\\"\\n   849→   fi\\n   850→   ```\\n   851→\\n   852→#### Expected Outcome\\n   853→- Agent's commit is present in history\\n   854→- Checkpoint trailer added (via deferred finalization)\\n   855→- Metadata correctly references `agent_commit.go`\\n   856→\\n   857→---\\n   858→\\n   859→### Test 15: Scenario 3 – Multiple Granular Commits\\n   860→\\n   861→**What it validates:** Agent making multiple granular commits in a single turn; each ge