 915→\\n   916→#### Expected Outcome\\n   917→- 3 new commits, each with a unique checkpoint ID\\n   918→- All three files exist\\n   919→- No shadow branches remain (all condensed)\\n   920→\\n   921→---\\n   922→\\n   923→### Test 16: Scenario 4 – User Splits Commits\\n   924→\\n   925→**What it validates:** User splitting agent changes across multiple commits, each getting its own checkpoint.\\n   926→\\n   927→**Corresponds to:** `TestE2E_Scenario4_UserSplitsCommits`\\n   928→\\n   929→#### Steps\\n   930→\\n   931→1. [Common Setup](#common-setup) with `manual-commit` strategy.\\n   932→\\n   933→2. **Start Droid** and type:\\n   934→   ```\\n   935→   Create these files:\\n   936→   1. fileA.go with content: package main; func A() string { return \\\"A\\\" }\\n   937→   2. fileB.go with content: package main; func B() string { return \\\"B\\\" }\\n   938→   3. fileC.go with content: package main; func C() string { return \\\"C\\\" }\\n   939→   4. fileD.go with content: package main; func D() string { return \\\"D\\\" }\\n   940→   Create all four files, no other files or actions.\\n   941→   ```\\n   942→\\n   943→3. **Exit Droid**, then verify all files exist:\\n   944→   ```bash\\n   945→   ls fileA.go fileB.go fileC.go fileD.go\\n   946→   ```\\n   947→\\n   948→4. **Commit only A and B first:**\\n   949→   ```bash\\n   950→   git add fileA.go fileB.go\\n   951→   git commit -m \\\"Add files A and B\\\"\\n   952→   CPID_AB=$(git log -1 --format=%B | grep \\\"Entire-Checkpoint:\\\" | awk '{print $2}')\\n   953→   echo \\\"Checkpoint A,B: $CPID_AB\\\"\\n   954→   ```\\n   955→\\n   956→5. **Commit C and D:**\\n   957→   ```bash\\n   958→   git add fileC.go fileD.go\\n   959→   git commit -m \\\"Add files C and D\\\"\\n   960→   CPID_CD=$(git log -1 --format=%B | grep \\\"Entire-Checkpoint:\\\" | awk '{print $2}')\\n   961→   echo \\\"Checkpoint C,D: $CPID_CD\\\"\\n   962→   ```\\n   963→\\n   964→6. **Verify unique checkpoint IDs:**\\n   965→   ```bash\\n   966→   [ \\\"$CPID_AB\\\" != \\\"$CPID_CD\\\" ] && echo \\\"PASS: Unique IDs\\\" || echo \\\"FAIL: Same ID\\\"\\n   967→   ```\\n   968→\\n   969→7. **Validate metadata for each checkpoint:**\\n   970→   ```bash\\n   971→   # First checkpoint (A, B)\\n   972→   SHARD=\\\"${CPID_AB:0:2}/${CPID_AB:2}\\\"\\n   973→   git show \\\"entire/checkpoints/v1:${SHARD}/metadata.json\\\" | jq '.files_touched'\\n   974→   # Should contain [\\\"fileA.go\\\", \\\"fileB.go\\\"]\\n   975→\\n   976→   # Second checkpoint (C, D)\\n   977→   SHARD=\\\"${CPID_CD:0:2}/${CPID_CD:2}\\\"\\n   978→   git show \\\"entire/checkpoints/v1:${SHARD}/metadata.json\\\" | jq '.files_touched'\\n   979→   # Should contain [\\\"fileC.go\\\", \\\"fileD.go\\\"]\\n   980→   ```\\n   981→\\n   982→8. **Verify no shadow branches remain:**\\n   983→   ```bash\\n   984→   git branch -a | grep \\\"entire/\\\" | grep -v \\\"checkpoints\\\"\\n   985→   # Should be empty\\n   986→   ```\\n   987→\\n   988→#### Expected Outcome\\n   989→- Two commits with unique checkpoint IDs\\n   990→- First checkpoint: `files_touched` = `[\\\"fileA.go\\\", \\\"fileB.go\\\"]`\\n   991→- Second checkpoint: `files_touched` = `[\\\"fileC.go\\\", \\\"fileD.go\\\"]`\\n   992→- No shadow branches remain\\n   993→\\n   994→---\\n   995→\\n   996→### Test 17: Scenario 5 – Partial Commit + Stash + Next Prompt\\n   997→\\n   998→**What it validates:** Partial commit, stash, new prompt with new files, commit new files.\\n   999→\\n  1000→**Corresponds to:** `TestE2E_Scenario5_PartialCommitStashNextPrompt`\\n  1001→\\n  1002→#### Steps\\n  1003→\\n  1004→1. [Common Setup](#common-setup) with `manual-commit` strategy.\\n  1005→\\n  1006→2. **Start Droid (Prompt 1):**\\n  1007→   ```\\n  1008→   Create these files:\\n  1009→   1. stash_a.go with content: package main; func StashA() {}\\n  1010→   2. stash_b.go with content: package main; func StashB() {}\\n  1011→   3. stash_c.go with content: package main; func StashC() {}\\n  1012→   Create all three files, nothing else.\\n  1013→   ```\\n  1014→\\n  1015→3. **Exit Droid**, commit A only:\\n  1016→   ```bash\\n  1017→   git add stash_a.go\\n  1018→   git commit -m \\\"Add stash_a\\\"\\n  1019→   ```\\n  1020→\\n  1021→4. **Stash remaining files:**\\n  1022→   ```bash\\n  1023→   git stash -u\\n  1024→   ls stash_b.go stash_c.go 2>/dev/null && echo \\\"FAIL: files should be stashed\\\" || echo \\\"PASS: files stashed\\\"\\n  1025→   ```\\n  1026→\\n  1027→5. **Start Droid again (Prompt 2):**\\n  1028→   ```\\n  1029→   Create these files:\\n  1030→   1. stash_d.go with content: package main; func StashD() {}\\n  1031→   2. stash_e.go with content: package main; func StashE() {}\\n  1032→   Create both files, nothing else.\\n  1033→   ```\\n  1034→\\n  1035→6. **Exit Droid**, commit D and E:\\n  1036→   ```bash\\n  1037→   git add stash_d.go stash_e.go\\n  1038→   git commit -m \\\"Add stash_d and stash_e\\\"\\n  1039→   ```\\n  1040→\\n  1041→7. **Verify both commits have checkpoint IDs:**\\n  1042→   ```bash\\n  1043→   git log --format=%B | grep \\\"Entire-Checkpoint:\\\" | awk '{print $2}'\\n  1044→   # Should show at least 2 unique IDs\\n  1045→   ```\\n  1046→\\n  1047→8. **Validate checkpoint metadata:**\\n  1048→   ```bash\\n  1049→   # Most recent checkpoint (D, E)\\n  1050→   CPID=$(git log -1 --format=%B | grep \\\"Entire-Checkpoint:\\\" | awk '{print $2}')\\n  1051→   SHARD=\\\"${CPID:0:2}/${CPID:2}\\\"\\n  1052→   git show \\\"entire/checkpoints/v1:${SHARD}/metadata.json\\\" | jq '.files_touched'\\n  1053→   # Should include stash_d.go and stash_e.go\\n  1054→   ```\\n  1055→\\n  1056→#### Expected Outcome\\n  1057→- First commit (A) has checkpoint\\n  1058→- Second commit (D, E) has checkpoint\\n  1059→- `files_touched` is correct for each checkpoint\\n  1060→- B and C remain stashed\\n  1061→\\n  1062→---\\n  1063→\\n  1064→### Test 18: Scenario 6 – Stash + Second Prompt + Unstash + Commit All\\n  1065→\\n  1066→**What it validates:** Stash,