}/${CPID:2}\\\"\\n  1122→   git show \\\"entire/checkpoints/v1:${SHARD}/metadata.json\\\" | jq '.files_touched'\\n  1123→   # Should include all 4 files: combo_b.go, combo_c.go, combo_d.go, combo_e.go\\n  1124→   ```\\n  1125→\\n  1126→9. **Verify no shadow branches remain:**\\n  1127→   ```bash\\n  1128→   git branch -a | grep \\\"entire/\\\" | grep -v \\\"checkpoints\\\"\\n  1129→   ```\\n  1130→\\n  1131→#### Expected Outcome\\n  1132→- Combined commit has all 4 files in `files_touched`\\n  1133→- Two unique checkpoint IDs across the two commits\\n  1134→- No shadow branches remain\\n  1135→\\n  1136→---\\n  1137→\\n  1138→### Test 19: Scenario 7 – Partial Staging (Simulated)\\n  1139→\\n  1140→**What it validates:** Content-aware carry-forward detects partial commits via hash comparison.\\n  1141→\\n  1142→**Corresponds to:** `TestE2E_Scenario7_PartialStagingSimulated`\\n  1143→\\n  1144→#### Steps\\n  1145→\\n  1146→1. [Common Setup](#common-setup) with `manual-commit` strategy.\\n  1147→\\n  1148→2. **Create a placeholder file and commit it (so it's a tracked/modified file):**\\n  1149→   ```bash\\n  1150→   echo 'package main\\n  1151→\\n  1152→   // placeholder' > partial.go\\n  1153→   git add partial.go\\n  1154→   git commit -m \\\"Add placeholder partial.go\\\"\\n  1155→   ```\\n  1156→\\n  1157→3. **Start Droid** and type:\\n  1158→   ```\\n  1159→   Replace the contents of partial.go with this exact content:\\n  1160→   package main\\n  1161→\\n  1162→   func First() int { return 1 }\\n  1163→   func Second() int { return 2 }\\n  1164→   func Third() int { return 3 }\\n  1165→   func Fourth() int { return 4 }\\n  1166→\\n  1167→   Replace the file with exactly this content, nothing else.\\n  1168→   ```\\n  1169→\\n  1170→4. **Exit Droid**, then save the full content:\\n  1171→   ```bash\\n  1172→   cp partial.go partial_full.go  # Backup\\n  1173→   ```\\n  1174→\\n  1175→5. **Write partial content (first two functions only) and commit:**\\n  1176→   ```bash\\n  1177→   cat > partial.go << 'EOF'\\n  1178→   package main\\n  1179→\\n  1180→   func First() int {\\n  1181→   \\treturn 1\\n  1182→   }\\n  1183→\\n  1184→   func Second() int {\\n  1185→   \\treturn 2\\n  1186→   }\\n  1187→   EOF\\n  1188→\\n  1189→   git add partial.go\\n  1190→   git commit -m \\\"Add first two functions\\\"\\n  1191→   ```\\n  1192→\\n  1193→6. **Restore the full content and commit the rest:**\\n  1194→   ```bash\\n  1195→   cp partial_full.go partial.go\\n  1196→   git add partial.go\\n  1197→   git commit -m \\\"Add remaining functions\\\"\\n  1198→   ```\\n  1199→\\n  1200→7. **Verify both commits have unique checkpoint IDs:**\\n  1201→   ```bash\\n  1202→   git log --format=%B | grep \\\"Entire-Checkpoint:\\\" | awk '{print $2}' | sort -u\\n  1203→   # Should show 2 unique IDs\\n  1204→   ```\\n  1205→\\n  1206→#### Expected Outcome\\n  1207→- Both commits get checkpoint trailers\\n  1208→- Checkpoint IDs are unique\\n  1209→- Content-aware carry-forward detects partial commit (hash mismatch)\\n  1210→\\n  1211→---\\n  1212→\\n  1213→## Content-Aware Detection Tests\\n  1214→\\n  1215→### Test 20: ContentAwareOverlap_RevertAndReplace\\n  1216→\\n  1217→**What it validates:** When user reverts agent's new file and writes completely different content, NO checkpoint trailer is added.\\n  1218→\\n  1219→**Corresponds to:** `TestE2E_ContentAwareOverlap_RevertAndReplace`\\n  1220→\\n  1221→#### Steps\\n  1222→\\n  1223→1. [Common Setup](#common-setup) with `manual-commit` strategy.\\n  1224→\\n  1225→2. **Start Droid** and type:\\n  1226→   ```\\n  1227→   Create a file called overlap_test.go with this exact content:\\n  1228→   package main\\n  1229→\\n  1230→   func OverlapOriginal() string {\\n  1231→   \\treturn \\\"original content from agent\\\"\\n  1232→   }\\n  1233→\\n  1234→   Create only this file.\\n  1235→   ```\\n  1236→\\n  1237→3. **Exit Droid**, verify rewind points:\\n  1238→   ```bash\\n  1239→   entire rewind --list | jq 'length'  # At least 1\\n  1240→   ```\\n  1241→\\n  1242→4. **Revert and write completely different content:**\\n  1243→   ```bash\\n  1244→   cat > overlap_test.go << 'EOF'\\n  1245→   package main\\n  1246→\\n  1247→   func CompletelyDifferent() string {\\n  1248→   \\treturn \\\"user wrote this, not the agent\\\"\\n  1249→   }\\n  1250→   EOF\\n  1251→   ```\\n  1252→\\n  1253→5. **Commit:**\\n  1254→   ```bash\\n  1255→   git add overlap_test.go\\n  1256→   git commit -m \\\"Add overlap test file\\\"\\n  1257→   ```\\n  1258→\\n  1259→6. **Verify NO checkpoint trailer was added:**\\n  1260→   ```bash\\n  1261→   git log -1 --format=%B | grep \\\"Entire-Checkpoint:\\\" && echo \\\"FAIL: Trailer should not exist\\\" || echo \\\"PASS: No trailer\\\"\\n  1262→   ```\\n  1263→\\n  1264→#### Expected Outcome\\n  1265→- Commit is made but has NO `Entire-Checkpoint` trailer\\n  1266→- Content-aware detection prevents linking because the user replaced the agent's content entirely (new file + content hash mismatch)\\n  1267→\\n  1268→---\\n  1269→\\n  1270→## Existing Files Tests\\n  1271→\\n  1272→### Test 21: ExistingFiles_ModifyAndCommit\\n  1273→\\n  1274→**What it validates:** Agent modifying an existing tracked file gets proper checkpoint.\\n  1275→\\n  1276→**Corresponds to:** `TestE2E_ExistingFiles_ModifyAndCommit`\\n  1277→\\n  1278→#### Steps\\n  1279→\\n  1280→1. [Common Setup](#common-setup) with `manual-commit` strategy.\\n  1281→\\n  1282→2. **Create and commit an initial file:**\\n  1283→   ```bash\\n  1284→   cat > config.go << 'EOF'\\n  1285→   package main\\n  1286→\\n  1287→   var Config = map[string]string{\\n  1288→   \\t\\\"version\\\": \\\"1.0\\\",\\n  1289→   }\\n  1290→   EOF\\n  1291→   git add config.go\\n  1292→   git commit -m \\\"Add initial config\\\"\\n  1293→   ```\\n  1294→\\n  1295→3. **Start Droid** and type:\\n  1296→   ```\\n  1297→   Modify the file config.go to add a new config key \\\"debug\\\" with value \\\"true\\\".\\n