ntroller.go\\n  1412→   git commit -m \\\"Add MVC scaffolding\\\"\\n  1413→   ```\\n  1414→\\n  1415→3. **Start Droid** and type:\\n  1416→   ```\\n  1417→   Add a Name field (string type) to each struct in these files:\\n  1418→   1. model.go - add Name string to Model struct\\n  1419→   2. view.go - add Name string to View struct\\n  1420→   3. controller.go - add Name string to Controller struct\\n  1421→   Only modify these three files.\\n  1422→   ```\\n  1423→\\n  1424→4. **Exit Droid**, then commit each file separately:\\n  1425→   ```bash\\n  1426→   git add model.go && git commit -m \\\"Add Name to Model\\\"\\n  1427→   CP_MODEL=$(git log -1 --format=%B | grep \\\"Entire-Checkpoint:\\\" | awk '{print $2}')\\n  1428→\\n  1429→   git add view.go && git commit -m \\\"Add Name to View\\\"\\n  1430→   CP_VIEW=$(git log -1 --format=%B | grep \\\"Entire-Checkpoint:\\\" | awk '{print $2}')\\n  1431→\\n  1432→   git add controller.go && git commit -m \\\"Add Name to Controller\\\"\\n  1433→   CP_CTRL=$(git log -1 --format=%B | grep \\\"Entire-Checkpoint:\\\" | awk '{print $2}')\\n  1434→\\n  1435→   echo \\\"Model: $CP_MODEL, View: $CP_VIEW, Controller: $CP_CTRL\\\"\\n  1436→   ```\\n  1437→\\n  1438→5. **Verify all three are unique:**\\n  1439→   ```bash\\n  1440→   [ \\\"$CP_MODEL\\\" != \\\"$CP_VIEW\\\" ] && [ \\\"$CP_VIEW\\\" != \\\"$CP_CTRL\\\" ] && [ \\\"$CP_MODEL\\\" != \\\"$CP_CTRL\\\" ] \\\\\\n  1441→     && echo \\\"PASS: All unique\\\" || echo \\\"FAIL\\\"\\n  1442→   ```\\n  1443→\\n  1444→6. **Verify metadata for each:**\\n  1445→   ```bash\\n  1446→   for CPID in $CP_MODEL $CP_VIEW $CP_CTRL; do\\n  1447→     SHARD=\\\"${CPID:0:2}/${CPID:2}\\\"\\n  1448→     echo \\\"--- Checkpoint $CPID ---\\\"\\n  1449→     git show \\\"entire/checkpoints/v1:${SHARD}/metadata.json\\\" | jq '.files_touched'\\n  1450→   done\\n  1451→   ```\\n  1452→\\n  1453→7. **Verify no shadow branches remain:**\\n  1454→   ```bash\\n  1455→   git branch -a | grep \\\"entire/\\\" | grep -v \\\"checkpoints\\\"\\n  1456→   ```\\n  1457→\\n  1458→#### Expected Outcome\\n  1459→- Three commits, each with unique checkpoint IDs\\n  1460→- Each checkpoint has correct `files_touched` (single file each)\\n  1461→- No shadow branches remain\\n  1462→\\n  1463→---\\n  1464→\\n  1465→### Test 24: ExistingFiles_RevertModification\\n  1466→\\n  1467→**What it validates:** Modified files (existing in HEAD) ALWAYS get checkpoints, even when user replaces content.\\n  1468→\\n  1469→**Corresponds to:** `TestE2E_ExistingFiles_RevertModification`\\n  1470→\\n  1471→#### Steps\\n  1472→\\n  1473→1. [Common Setup](#common-setup) with `manual-commit` strategy.\\n  1474→\\n  1475→2. **Create and commit a placeholder:**\\n  1476→   ```bash\\n  1477→   echo 'package main\\n  1478→\\n  1479→   // placeholder' > calc.go\\n  1480→   git add calc.go\\n  1481→   git commit -m \\\"Add placeholder\\\"\\n  1482→   ```\\n  1483→\\n  1484→3. **Start Droid** and type:\\n  1485→   ```\\n  1486→   Replace the contents of calc.go with this exact code:\\n  1487→   package main\\n  1488→\\n  1489→   func AgentMultiply(a, b int) int {\\n  1490→   \\treturn a * b\\n  1491→   }\\n  1492→\\n  1493→   Only modify calc.go, nothing else.\\n  1494→   ```\\n  1495→\\n  1496→4. **Exit Droid**, verify agent modified it:\\n  1497→   ```bash\\n  1498→   grep \\\"AgentMultiply\\\" calc.go && echo \\\"PASS\\\"\\n  1499→   ```\\n  1500→\\n  1501→5. **Revert and write completely different content:**\\n  1502→   ```bash\\n  1503→   cat > calc.go << 'EOF'\\n  1504→   package main\\n  1505→\\n  1506→   func UserAdd(x, y int) int {\\n  1507→   \\treturn x + y\\n  1508→   }\\n  1509→   EOF\\n  1510→   ```\\n  1511→\\n  1512→6. **Commit:**\\n  1513→   ```bash\\n  1514→   git add calc.go\\n  1515→   git commit -m \\\"Add user functions\\\"\\n  1516→   ```\\n  1517→\\n  1518→7. **Verify checkpoint IS present (modified files always get checkpoints):**\\n  1519→   ```bash\\n  1520→   git log -1 --format=%B | g